TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {86499=Founded in the middle of 1987 by two friend Greg “Scott” Swingrover and Chris “Mad Dog” Moeller, S&M Bikes was created to produce BMX Bikes that could deal with the use and abuse their founders and their friends could dish out. They originally made the K-9 D-Zine frame and forks for themselves. Then their friends wanted them too, so they made 25 framesets. From these beginnings, more than two decades ago, their goal has not changed – to make good bikes and run things their way. S&M will continue to sail the seas of BMX until other companies make bikes as good as theirs or it’s not fun anymore. Neither of which they feel looks likely to happen soon.}
